org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.internal.network

Class WifiDirectAgent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.internal.network.WifiStartStoppable
      • org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.internal.network.WifiDirectAgent

  • public class WifiDirectAgent
extends WifiStartStoppable
    {@link WifiDirectAgent provides *low-level* basic connectivity to Wifi Direct. Most importantly, this handles callback threading reasonably for us so we don't end up in deadlock situations with the main app thread.

      • setWifiP2pChannels

        public void setWifiP2pChannels(int lc,
                               int oc,
                               WifiP2pManager.ActionListener listener)
        setWifiP2pChannels is a hidden method that went in the AOSP tree on 2013.05.03, and so, we believe is included even in Kitcat.
        Parameters:
        lc - the channel to listen on. 0 = let supplicant pick (preferable)
        oc - operating channel. 0 = let platform pick, 1-14 - set per requirement and validity within regulatory domain
        listener - asynchronously receives results of setting
